<head>
  <title>ID and Class Example</title>
  <style>
    /* ID selector */
    #unique-box {
      background-color: lightblue;
      padding: 15px;
      border: 2px solid blue;
    }

    /* Class selector */
    .common-style {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      color: darkgreen;
      font-size: 18px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h2>5. ID & CLASS</h2>

  <div id="unique-box">
    This div uses an <strong>ID</strong> for unique styling.
  </div>

  <p class="common-style">This paragraph uses a <strong>class</strong> for reusable styling.</p>
  <p class="common-style">This is another paragraph with the same class.</p>

</body>
